         <lineage>
            <LI_Lineage>
               <statement>
                  <gco:CharacterString>There are specific obligations on Member States under the EC Birds and Habitats Directives to avoid the deterioration of the natural habitats of the species and significant disturbance of the species for which SPAs have been designated. These obligations are implemented through domestic legislation in the Conservation (Natural Habitats, &amp;c.) Regulations 1994, as amended.  

Designating Authority In Scotland
Scottish Ministers

Role of SNH
SNH acts as the advisor to Government in proposing selected sites for Ministerial approval as proposed SPAs. SNH then undertakes  consultation over proposed sites with owners, occupiers, planning authorities and other  interested parties on behalf of Scottish Ministers.   

Legislative Context
Article  4  of  the  EC  Directive  on  the Conservation of Wild Birds 1979 (EC/79/409, as  amended  30.8.85 and 8.5.91):  commonly known as the Birds Directive.  In  GB  the designation is generally underpinned through the  SSSI mechanism for terrestrial  sites; the  Government is proposing new provisions for marine SPAs.</gco:CharacterString>
               </statement>
            </LI_Lineage>
         </lineage>
